    "notes": "T1055.012 threadless injection (DLL function pointer overwrite) is distinguished from vanilla injection (T1055.001) by the absence of PROCESS_CREATE_THREAD (0x2) in GrantedAccess. Key detection signal: a non-system process from a user-writable path (AppData\\Local\\Temp) opening a system process with 0x1438 (VM_WRITE + VM_OPERATION present, CREATE_THREAD absent). Pair Sysmon EID 10 with EID 7 (ntdll.dll load by the same PID) to increase confidence. Benign tuning: exclude known AV/EDR vendors (MsMpEng.exe, MBAMService.exe) and WerFault.exe by process.executable path prefix, and require process.executable to match a user-writable directory pattern."
  },
